# Analysis of Main Target Image

The image shows two separate structures:

## Structure 1 (Left):
- Total blocks: 7 blocks
- Layers: 3 layers
- Bottom layer: 3 red blocks forming a base with arches (2 arch blocks on sides, 1 cube in middle)
- Middle layer: 1 yellow rectangular beam across the arches
- Top layer: 1 red block with an arch opening and 2 orange triangular roof pieces

## Structure 2 (Right):
- Total blocks: 5 blocks
- Layers: 3 layers (including triangular pieces)
- Main body: 2 green cubes stacked vertically
- Accessory pieces: 3 orange triangular pieces forming a roof and wings

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

For Structure 1:
- Block #1 (red arch piece)
- Block #2 (red arch piece, opposite orientation)
- Block #8 (red cube)
- Block #10 (yellow rectangular beam)
- Block #4 (red block with vertical cutout)
- Block #13 and #14 (orange triangular roof pieces)

For Structure 2:
- Block #7 (green cube) - used twice
- Block #13 (orange triangular piece) for roof
- Block #15 and #16 (orange triangular pieces) for side "wings"

# Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 2
    Step3: Move block with index 8
    Step4: Move block with index 10
    Step5: Move block with index 4
    Step6: Move block with index 13
    Step7: Move block with index 14
    Step8: Move block with index 7
    Step9: Move block with index 7
    Step10: Move block with index 13
    Step11: Move block with index 15
    Step12: Move block with index 16
}
```

This assembly sequence first builds the left structure from the bottom up (steps 1-7), then builds the right structure (steps 8-12).
